b'TL;DR: The 5-Step Framework to release depression using intention.  \xe2\x80\xa2 Accept \xe2\x80\xa2 Decide \xe2\x80\xa2\xc2\xa0Set \xe2\x80\xa2\xc2\xa0Start \xe2\x80\xa2\xc2\xa0Celebrate  I used this to write weekly for a year, during the midst of depression. b"The reason this framework works so well is because it helps you to stop identifying with depression.  So, don't fall into the trap of fighting the emotion. Allow yourself to feel it. Give yourself the grace to be human.  Then be intentional about something else and build on it."

b"Step 1: Accept depression.  Most people think we should fight depression.  Instead, label depression as emotion, grab a pencil and paper, and write w/o judgement.  If you do this, here's what happens:  \xe2\x80\xa2 You allow yourself to feel it \xe2\x80\xa2 You release it \xe2\x80\xa2\xc2\xa0It no longer holds you"

b"Two years ago, I was depressed, standing at the edge of a balcony.  Then, I decided to stop fighting depression, and instead focus on intention.  Here's the 5-Step framework I use to work with depression and ultimately, not identify with it.  \xf0\x9f\xa7\xb5\xf0\x9f\x91\x87"
